 of Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Scotland, United Kingdom","Stornoway, Isle of Lewis, Ross and Cromarty, Scotland":"Stornoway, Ross and Cromarty, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Morrison","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: from <i>Ó Muirgheasáin</i> ‘descendant of <i>Muirgheasán</i>’, a diminutive of <i>Muirgheas</i>, a personal name meaning ‘sea valor’.","Scottish: from Gaelic <b>Mac Moireasdain</b> ‘son of <i>Moireasdan</i>’, a personal name cognate with Irish <i>Muirgheasán</i>’ (see 1 above).","Scottish and English: patronymic from the personal name   Morris  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Morrisson","meanings":["English: variant of   Morrison  ."]},{"name":"Morson","meanings":["English, Scottish and Irish: shortened form of   Morrison  .","English: sometimes a variant of <b>Moorsom</b>, a habitational name from Moorsholm in North Yorkshire. The placename derives from Old English <i>mōr</i> ‘moor’ + <i>hūsum</i>, dative plural form of <i>hūs</i> ‘house’."]},{"name":"Morison","meanings":["Scottish (northern): variant of   Morrison  ."]},{"name":"Morris","meanings":["English and Scottish: from <i>Maurice</i>, an Old French personal name introduced to Britain by the Normans. It is derived from Latin <i>Mauritius</i>, a derivative of <i>Maurus</i> (see   Moore  ). This was the name of several early Christian saints. In some cases it may be a nickname of the same derivation for someone with a swarthy complexion.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Muirghis</b>, a variant of <b>Ó Muirgheasa</b> (see   Morrissey  ).","Welsh: Anglicized form of the personal name <i>Meurig</i> (from Latin <i>Mauritius</i>), which was gradually superseded in Wales by <i>Morus</i>, <i>Morys</i>, a derivative of the Anglo-Norman French form of the name (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"McCorriston","meanings":["Scottish (Wigtownshire): probably from <b>Mac Thoireasdain</b> ‘son of <i>Tòireasdan</i> or <i>Tòrasdan</i>’, a Gaelicized form of the Old Norse name <i>Thórrsteinn</i> ‘thunder stone’. It may also be from a lenited form of Gaelic <b>Mac Moireasdain</b> ‘son of <i>Moireasdan</i>’; see   Morrison  ."]}]},{"name":"Ewen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual Anglicized form in Scotland and Northern Ireland of Gaelic Eóghan . It is also found in northern England from the 14th century onwards, and since the late 1990s has been one of the Gaelic names that enjoy wider currency."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ewen Morrison was born in 1474, in Stornoway, Ross and Cromarty, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Morris MacGilles, was 24 and his mother, Mrs. Morris MacGilles, was 22. He married Margaret Peggy McInnes about 1494, in Edinburgh, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1521, in Edinburgh, Scotland, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1474–1521":"1474–1521","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","1478–1500":"1478–1500","1495–1550":"1495–1550","1510–Female":"1510–Surnud","1450–Male":"1450–Surnud","1452–Female":"1452–Surnud","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1510":"1510","1521":"1521","1474":"1474","1452":"1452","1495":"1495","1473":"1473","1550":"1550","1450":"1450","1470":"1470","about 1494":"umbes 1494","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Scotland","Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland":"Isle of Lewis, Ross-shire, Scotland","Edinburgh, City of Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Edinburgh, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Stornoway, Isle of Lewis, Ross and Cromarty, Scotland":"Stornoway, Ross and Cromarty, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1474–1521":"1474–1521","1470–Male":"1470–Kuollut","1478–1500":"1478–1500","1495–1550":"1495–1550","1510–Female":"1510–Kuollut","1450–Male":"1450–Kuollut","1452–Female":"1452–Kuollut","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1510":"1510","1521":"1521","1474":"1474","1452":"145